{"parse":{"title":"Neumann series","pageid":2533545,"revid":843287372,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>Neumann series</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Series_(mathematics)\" title=\"Series (mathematics)\">mathematical series</a> of the form\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\sum _{k=0}^{\\infty }T^{k}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\sum _{k=0}^{\\infty }T^{k}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b8b1b572825e351b185d3b5d2c7aade8b8c8135c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:6.551ex; height:7.009ex;\" alt=\"\\sum _{k=0}^{\\infty }T^{k}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>where <i>T</i> is an <a href=\"/wiki/Operator_(mathematics)\" title=\"Operator (mathematics)\">operator</a>. Hence, <i>T<sup>k</sup></i> is a mathematical notation for <i>k</i> consecutive operations of the operator <i>T</i>. This generalizes the <a href=\"/wiki/Geometric_series\" title=\"Geometric series\">geometric series</a>.\n</p><p>The series is named after the mathematician <a href=\"/wiki/Carl_Neumann\" title=\"Carl Neumann\">Carl Neumann</a>, who used it in 1877 in the context of <a href=\"/wiki/Potential_theory\" title=\"Potential theory\">potential theory</a>. The Neumann series is used in <a href=\"/wiki/Functional_analysis\" title=\"Functional analysis\">functional analysis</a>. It forms the basis of the <a href=\"/wiki/Liouville-Neumann_series\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Liouville-Neumann series\">Liouville-Neumann series</a>, which is used to solve <a href=\"/wiki/Fredholm_integral_equation\" title=\"Fredholm integral equation\">Fredholm integral equations</a>. It is also important when studying the <a href=\"/wiki/Spectrum_(functional_analysis)\" title=\"Spectrum (functional analysis)\">spectrum</a> of bounded operators.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Properties\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Properties</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Example\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Example</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#The_set_of_invertible_operators_is_open\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The set of invertible operators is open</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Properties\">Properties</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Neumann_series&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Properties\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Suppose that <i>T</i> is a bounded linear operator on the <a href=\"/wiki/Normed_vector_space\" title=\"Normed vector space\">normed vector space</a> <i>X</i>. If the Neumann series <a href=\"/wiki/Convergent_series\" title=\"Convergent series\">converges</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/Operator_norm\" title=\"Operator norm\">operator norm</a>, then Id \u2013 <i>T</i> is <a href=\"/wiki/Invertible_matrix\" title=\"Invertible matrix\">invertible</a> and its inverse is the series:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle (\\mathrm {Id} -T)^{-1}=\\sum _{k=0}^{\\infty }T^{k}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle (\\mathrm {Id} -T)^{-1}=\\sum _{k=0}^{\\infty }T^{k}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/51f33ca57f45e2f8fe205447a1a7bedd8bcf9691\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:20.4ex; height:7.009ex;\" alt=\"(\\mathrm {Id} -T)^{-1}=\\sum _{k=0}^{\\infty }T^{k}\"/></span>,</dd></dl>\n<p>where <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Id} }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {Id} }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c09865da84a517ba0262ecec90529728028101f6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.132ex; height:2.176ex;\" alt=\"\\mathrm {Id} \"/></span> is the <a href=\"/wiki/Identity_operator\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Identity operator\">identity operator</a> in <i>X</i>.  To see why, consider the partial sums\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle S_{n}:=\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>:=</mo>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle S_{n}:=\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/37bfca859c1f0246a521e185ad8cd95d05d76336\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:12.939ex; height:7.009ex;\" alt=\"S_{n}:=\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k}\"/></span>.</dd></dl>\n<p>Then we have\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }(\\mathrm {Id} -T)S_{n}=\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }\\left(\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k}-\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k+1}\\right)=\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }\\left(\\mathrm {Id} -T^{n+1}\\right)=\\mathrm {Id} .}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <munder>\n          <mo movablelimits=\"true\" form=\"prefix\">lim</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">&#x2192;<!-- \u2192 --></mo>\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munder>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munder>\n          <mo movablelimits=\"true\" form=\"prefix\">lim</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">&#x2192;<!-- \u2192 --></mo>\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munder>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <munderover>\n              <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mn>0</mn>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>n</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </munderover>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>T</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <munderover>\n              <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mn>0</mn>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>n</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </munderover>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>T</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munder>\n          <mo movablelimits=\"true\" form=\"prefix\">lim</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">&#x2192;<!-- \u2192 --></mo>\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munder>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi>\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>T</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>n</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }(\\mathrm {Id} -T)S_{n}=\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }\\left(\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k}-\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k+1}\\right)=\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }\\left(\\mathrm {Id} -T^{n+1}\\right)=\\mathrm {Id} .}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8250254fb44c7e3cd4b51383a26256fbf6d93c4c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:70.593ex; height:7.509ex;\" alt=\"\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }(\\mathrm {Id} -T)S_{n}=\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }\\left(\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k}-\\sum _{k=0}^{n}T^{k+1}\\right)=\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }\\left(\\mathrm {Id} -T^{n+1}\\right)=\\mathrm {Id} .\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>This result on operators is analogous to <a href=\"/wiki/Geometric_series\" title=\"Geometric series\">geometric series</a> in <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\mathbb {R} }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\mathbb {R} }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/786849c765da7a84dbc3cce43e96aad58a5868dc\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.678ex; height:2.176ex;\" alt=\"\\mathbb {R} \"/></span>, in which we find that:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\frac {1}{1-x}}=1+x+x^{2}+\\cdots }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \u22ef --></mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\frac {1}{1-x}}=1+x+x^{2}+\\cdots }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/68fbe8705d55a6116699d41c455ff459667674b4\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:25.388ex; height:5.343ex;\" alt=\"{\\frac {1}{1-x}}=1+x+x^{2}+\\cdots \"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>One case in which convergence is guaranteed is when <i>X</i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Banach_space\" title=\"Banach space\">Banach space</a> and |<i>T</i>| &lt; 1 in the operator norm. However, there are also results which give weaker conditions under which the series converges.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Example\">Example</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Neumann_series&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Example\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Let <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle C\\in \\mathbb {R} ^{3\\times 3}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2208;<!-- \u2208 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>3</mn>\n            <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \u00d7 --></mo>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle C\\in \\mathbb {R} ^{3\\times 3}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b3676cfe1b12ade71eafe341659e41fe6c287245\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:9.44ex; height:2.676ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle C\\in \\mathbb {R} ^{3\\times 3}}\"/></span> be given by:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\begin{pmatrix}0&amp;{\\frac {1}{2}}&amp;{\\frac {1}{4}}\\\\{\\frac {5}{7}}&amp;0&amp;{\\frac {1}{7}}\\\\{\\frac {3}{10}}&amp;{\\frac {3}{5}}&amp;0\\end{pmatrix}}.}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mfrac>\n                      <mn>1</mn>\n                      <mn>2</mn>\n                    </mfrac>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mfrac>\n                      <mn>1</mn>\n                      <mn>4</mn>\n                    </mfrac>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mfrac>\n                      <mn>5</mn>\n                      <mn>7</mn>\n                    </mfrac>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mfrac>\n                      <mn>1</mn>\n                      <mn>7</mn>\n                    </mfrac>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mfrac>\n                      <mn>3</mn>\n                      <mn>10</mn>\n                    </mfrac>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mfrac>\n                      <mn>3</mn>\n                      <mn>5</mn>\n                    </mfrac>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n            </mtable>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\begin{pmatrix}0&amp;{\\frac {1}{2}}&amp;{\\frac {1}{4}}\\\\{\\frac {5}{7}}&amp;0&amp;{\\frac {1}{7}}\\\\{\\frac {3}{10}}&amp;{\\frac {3}{5}}&amp;0\\end{pmatrix}}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/298f9b73421349a55c488f285ae3bc674ac97d58\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -5.338ex; width:15.907ex; height:11.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\begin{pmatrix}0&amp;{\\frac {1}{2}}&amp;{\\frac {1}{4}}\\\\{\\frac {5}{7}}&amp;0&amp;{\\frac {1}{7}}\\\\{\\frac {3}{10}}&amp;{\\frac {3}{5}}&amp;0\\end{pmatrix}}.}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>We need to show that C is smaller than unity in some <a href=\"/wiki/Matrix_norm\" title=\"Matrix norm\">norm</a>. Therefore, we calculate:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}||C||_{\\infty }&amp;=\\max _{i}\\sum _{j}|c_{ij}|=\\max \\left\\lbrace {\\frac {3}{4}},{\\frac {6}{7}},{\\frac {9}{10}}\\right\\rbrace ={\\frac {9}{10}}&lt;1.\\end{aligned}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mtable columnalign=\"right left right left right left right left right left right left\" rowspacing=\"3pt\" columnspacing=\"0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em\" displaystyle=\"true\">\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mi>C</mi>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <msub>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n              </mtd>\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <munder>\n                  <mo movablelimits=\"true\" form=\"prefix\">max</mo>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </munder>\n                <munder>\n                  <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi>j</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </munder>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi>c</mi>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                    <mi>j</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mo movablelimits=\"true\" form=\"prefix\">max</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>{</mo>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                      <mfrac>\n                        <mn>3</mn>\n                        <mn>4</mn>\n                      </mfrac>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mo>,</mo>\n                    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                      <mfrac>\n                        <mn>6</mn>\n                        <mn>7</mn>\n                      </mfrac>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mo>,</mo>\n                    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                      <mfrac>\n                        <mn>9</mn>\n                        <mn>10</mn>\n                      </mfrac>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mo>}</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mfrac>\n                    <mn>9</mn>\n                    <mn>10</mn>\n                  </mfrac>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>&lt;</mo>\n                <mn>1.</mn>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n          </mtable>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}||C||_{\\infty }&amp;=\\max _{i}\\sum _{j}|c_{ij}|=\\max \\left\\lbrace {\\frac {3}{4}},{\\frac {6}{7}},{\\frac {9}{10}}\\right\\rbrace ={\\frac {9}{10}}&lt;1.\\end{aligned}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7329323f519d183b94974842ec08b9685085a6f8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.838ex; width:54.003ex; height:6.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}||C||_{\\infty }&amp;=\\max _{i}\\sum _{j}|c_{ij}|=\\max \\left\\lbrace {\\frac {3}{4}},{\\frac {6}{7}},{\\frac {9}{10}}\\right\\rbrace ={\\frac {9}{10}}&lt;1.\\end{aligned}}}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>Thus, we know from the statement above that <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle (I-C)^{-1}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>I</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle (I-C)^{-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/11ae02676f1318a2f684bda06bcb1a5e7c909a71\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:9.921ex; height:3.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle (I-C)^{-1}}\"/></span> exists.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_set_of_invertible_operators_is_open\">The set of invertible operators is open</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Neumann_series&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: The set of invertible operators is open\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A corollary is that the set of invertible operators between two Banach spaces <i>B</i> and <i>B'</i> is open in the topology induced by the operator norm. Indeed, let <i>S</i>&#160;: <i>B</i> &#8594; <i>B</i>' be an invertible operator and let <i>T</i>: <i>B</i> &#8594; <i>B</i>' be another operator. If |<i>S</i> \u2013 <i>T</i> | &lt; |<i>S</i><sup>\u22121</sup>|<sup>\u22121</sup>, then <i>T</i> is also invertible. This follows by writing <i>T</i> as\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T=S(\\mathrm {Id} -(\\mathrm {Id} -S^{-1}T))\\,}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>S</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T=S(\\mathrm {Id} -(\\mathrm {Id} -S^{-1}T))\\,}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0e7c3396df6b56a89ef264a80ef7c88965b0c1e9\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:25.675ex; height:3.176ex;\" alt=\"T=S(\\mathrm {Id} -(\\mathrm {Id} -S^{-1}T))\\,\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>and applying the result in the previous section on the second factor. The norm of <i>T</i><sup>\u22121</sup> can be bounded by\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle |T^{-1}|\\leq {\\tfrac {1}{1-q}}|S^{-1}|\\quad {\\text{where}}\\quad q=|S-T|\\,|S^{-1}|.}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2264;<!-- \u2264 --></mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n                <mi>q</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mstyle>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"1em\" />\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mtext>where</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"1em\" />\n        <mi>q</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>S</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle |T^{-1}|\\leq {\\tfrac {1}{1-q}}|S^{-1}|\\quad {\\text{where}}\\quad q=|S-T|\\,|S^{-1}|.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2f431c6cd853e4340d02549745c0f8966a3368c9\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.505ex; width:45.498ex; height:3.843ex;\" alt=\"|T^{-1}|\\leq {\\tfrac {1}{1-q}}|S^{-1}|\\quad {\\text{where}}\\quad q=|S-T|\\,|S^{-1}|.\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Neumann_series&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Werner, Dirk (2005). <i>Funktionalanalysis</i> (in German). Springer Verlag. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/3-540-43586-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/3-540-43586-7\">3-540-43586-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;